Cabbage Patch Settlement. Serving children and families of the Cabbage Patch, as the neighborhood was known at the time.
Conrad-Caldwell House. Theophilus Conrad, tannery owner, built this home 1893-95. Designed by Clarke & Loomis architects in Richardsonian Romanesque style.
The Witch Tree is a vernacular art installation at the corner of 6th & Ormsby in Old Louisville. It consists of a modified tree that includes facial features, text, and spooky decorations.
